\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Per-configuration scatter of $P(M^\star |R^\star )$ vs.\ $P(C^\star |M^\star )$ at three cadences. The strong negative correlation at $K=4$ (Pearson $-0.61$) is the bottleneck-shift signature: the same configurations that succeed at $M$ tend to fail at $C$ and vice versa. The correlation decays to noise by $K=64$.}}{18}{figure.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:jensen-scatter}{{8}{18}{Per-configuration scatter of $P(M^\star |R^\star )$ vs.\ $P(C^\star |M^\star )$ at three cadences. The strong negative correlation at $K=4$ (Pearson $-0.61$) is the bottleneck-shift signature: the same configurations that succeed at $M$ tend to fail at $C$ and vice versa. The correlation decays to noise by $K=64$}{figure.8}{}}
